calculationPeriod.value: Annually, from October 5 to October 5 of the consecutive year

paymentDates.value: Annually, 2 business days after October 5, commencing on October 7, 2011, and ending on October 7, 2015

resetDates.value: October 5 of each year, commencing on October 5, 2011, and ending on October 5, 2015

fixingDates.value: 2 business days prior to the reset date

riskDisclosure.value: Interest rate risk, credit risk, and liquidity risk

representations.value: Each party represents to the other party that it has the power to enter into this contract and to perform its obligations under it.

notices.value: All notices under this contract shall be in writing and shall be delivered to the other party at its address specified in the contract.

amendments.value: This contract may be amended only in writing signed by both parties.

termination.value: This contract may be terminated only in accordance with its terms.

waiver.value: Any waiver by one party of any provision of this contract shall not be deemed a waiver of any other provision.

entireAgreement.value: This contract constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior negotiations, understandings, and agreements between them.
